The paper deals with digitalization of line segments in the plane, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The approach presented involves deriving a system of digital segments from a total order on the integers, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the Hausdorff metric, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions an explicit construction, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
